dismissalComment.html: back of a length outside off, a bit of extra bounce, and Rohit goes for 99! It hurried through quicker than he expected, perhaps, as he looked to dab it towards third man, and he looks distraught when the caught behind appeal is upheld. Snicko shows the faintest of nicks, though.

headshotImage.caption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: what a splendid catch that is from Shaun Marsh. A nothing delivery from Hastings, short and wide. Dhawna comes down and belts the cut in the air to deep point. He errs though and fails to keep it down. Shaun marsh runs around and leaps to take the ball over his head, both feet off the ground. And hold son despite landing hard. Is that what Australia need? Dhawan has thrown away a really really good start

commentPreTextItems.html: Every fielder is in the circle now

commentTextItems.html: and it's all over. Full outside off and Pandey launches this over the covers. Doesn't really middle it, but all he needs to do is clear the infield, and that's what he does

commentPostTextItems.html: 10.30pm Phew. What a game to end this ODI series. We'll soon have reports and analysis of everything that happened up on our site. Do take a look when they go up. The T20 series begins on Tuesday - make sure you tune in for that as well. Until then, goodbye!

Steven Smith: "It's been a pretty big run-scoring feast. Very proud of the way the players have played in this series. Tonight was a masterclass in chasing [from India]. We missed a few opportunities in the field, but that happens in cricket, but we have to move on and improve. [The T20s] are a different format, and there is a World Cup around the corner, so the boys are raring to go."

MS Dhoni: "I think we have been competitive in the series. The goal was to win matches. The first four games, I thought were close, but we didn't close it down well. That's important in the ODI format. Every over matters especially in a high-scoring game. Giving those 15-20-run overs, it becomes slightly easier for the opposition. The top order has been together for a long time now. Where we have been hurt a little bit is the lower-order batting, where Manish did really well today, and also the fact that we have not had a settled bowling attack. We have to improve our fielding slightly. Grounds over here are quite big, and once you know the fielder is not that quick or doesn't have a good fielder, you will put pressure on that fielder."

Rohit Sharma is the man of the series. "Not really [frustrating to get out on 99], because we won the game tonight. Young Manish Pandey did really well, playing his fourth one-day international, getting that hundred and getting us off the mark. Over the course of the tournament we played some really good cricket. Little moments we couldn't capitalise on. We never thought we were 4-0 down. We wanted to come and win this game and go with a positive frame of mind into the T20 series. I've been batting really well in one-day cricket, it's important that I keep scoring runs for the team."

10.25pm Presentation time. Manish Pandey is the man of the match. "Batting No. 4 is one of the chances I got because Ajju was injured, and I wanted to capitalise, especially on these wickets, with 300 scored in every match. Always nice to have Indian people in the stadium, it's a big boost to us."

PrabodhR.: "This win again proved cricket is a team game. Even after an off day of Umesh and Kohli, first excellent bowling by Bumrahh and Ishant in death , good start, excellent middle and lower order batting.. Remarkable performance by whole team especially Manish Pandey played a superb knock under pressure."

Mustafa Moudi: "Maxwell scored 29 runs in last 2 overs of the last match which hurt india in the last match. On the other hand, Marsh scored just 7 runs off last 2 overs and it hurt Australia. So each run in Cricket Matters !!!" -- Credit for that has to go to Bumrah and Ishant Sharma, who bowled two excellent overs at the death.

10.12pm This is the first successful 300-plus chase against Australia in Australia. India will feel they should have crossed off that achievement in the previous game itself, but they've done it here, and they've done it with six wickets in hand. Superb innings from Pandey, came in when India had lost a bit of impetus with the quick wickets of Shikhar Dhawan and Virat Kohli, but he kept his cool, played his shots, and stayed there till the end. Don't forget Rohit Sharma's 99 either. Another excellent innings to go past 400 runs in the series and 5000 in ODIs.

commentPreTextItems.html: Gurkeerat Singh at the non-striker's end. Six to get off four balls.

commentTextItems.html: shot. That's full outside off, a wide yorker, almost, and Pandey, cool as a cucumber, brings up his hundred in style. Lets it come on, opens his bat face at impact, and steers it fine to the third man boundary. This has been an outstanding one-day innings

dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni c Warner b MR Marsh 34 (42b 1x4 1x6 64m) SR: 80.95

commentTextItems.html: full and wide and Dhoni goes after it and holes out, Warner takes a simple catch running in from long-off. They cross over, however, and Pandey will be on strike

bam! That's a low full-toss outside off, in Dhoni's slot, but in this innings he hasn't been middling anything. He doesn't middle this either, but he just about clears the leaping long-off fielder. Warner is the fielder. He would have needed to be as tall as Mohammad Irfan to take that

commentPreTextItems.html: Thirteen from six balls. Mitchell Marsh is under pressure, and Dhoni, though his face will not show it, is probably under even more pressure. Pandey, in the midst of all this, is on 98.
Vivek Kashyap: "Australia's last two low scoring overs could prove costly here"

commentTextItems.html: full and wide, and it's given wide after Dhoni leaves it alone. Harsh call, seemed to be just inside the tramline, though, as Wasim Akram reminds us on TV commentary - the line is just an indication
down the track, Faulkner follows him, and he tucks it away through backward square leg and picks up two, leaving Dhoni at strike at the start of the last over

commentTextItems.html: down the track and Pandey is an absolute genius at landing the ball short of deep fielders. Takes his bottom hand off the handle while chasing the full, wide slower ball, and it drops short of the sweeper cover fielder running to his right
sees him making room and follows him. Slogs at it, misses, and it ricochets off the pad into the off side
full-toss on leg stump, Dhoni lap-sweeps towards long leg
down the track, looks to make room. Faulkner denies him the room with the slower ball and he slogs it out to deep midwicket, on the bounce

commentPreTextItems.html: 22 from 2. Dhoni on strike. Here's Faulkner.

commentTextItems.html: full on middle and leg, clips to midwicket, who's slightly deep and allows a reasonably comfortable single
full outside off, slower ball. Dhoni slogs and inside-edges towards short fine leg

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Manish Pandey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Manish Pandey player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: full and wide and this time Dhoni is right where he needs to be. Huge backlift, flat-bats it down the ground, absolutely smashes it and long-off has no chance going to his right
down the track and he  gets too close to this ball from Marsh. Jabs it down towards long-off, and the electric Pandey turns quickly to complete the second, but a direct hit would have done for him
slower short ball outside off, wide of Pandey who's moved across his stumps. Chopped down towards backward point
wide yorker and Pandey reaches out and makes vital contact, looks to squeeze it away through point, gets an outside edge that runs away to the third man boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: Mitchell Marsh has two overs left, and Faulkner one. They'll probably bowl the last three.

commentTextItems.html: fullish, wide of off, flat-batted to long-off
full on leg stump, clipped firmly but straight to midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: Only five from that over. 35 to get now, from three overs.

dismissalComment.html: got him. That's a fullish ball slanting away wide of off stump. Wade looked to thrash his arms through it, having taken a big step back to shorten the length, and only succeeds in top-edging to Dhoni

headshotImage.caption: Jasprit Bumrah player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jasprit Bumrah player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: James Faulkner b Bumrah 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: oh, Bumrah, what a delivery. Takes out Faulkner's off stump with a perfect yorker that the batsman plays all around

headshotImage.caption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma c Wade b Hastings 99 (108b 9x4 1x6 142m) SR: 91.66

dismissalComment.html: back of a length outside off, a bit of extra bounce, and Rohit goes for 99! It hurried through quicker than he expected, perhaps, as he looked to dab it towards third man, and he looks distraught when the caught behind appeal is upheld. Snicko shows the faintest of nicks, though.

headshotImage.caption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shikhar Dhawan c SE Marsh b Hastings 78 (56b 7x4 3x6 69m) SR: 139.28

dismissalComment.html: what a splendid catch that is from Shaun Marsh. A nothing delivery from Hastings, short and wide. Dhawna comes down and belts the cut in the air to deep point. He errs though and fails to keep it down. Shaun marsh runs around and leaps to take the ball over his head, both feet off the ground. And hold son despite landing hard. Is that what Australia need? Dhawan has thrown away a really really good start

headshotImage.caption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Wade b Hastings 8 (11b 1x4 0x6 11m) SR: 72.72

dismissalComment.html: out! Big, big wicket this. Very full and wide from Hastings. Kohli goes for the expansive drive and gets a thin nick through to the keeper. Wade takes it over his head. Australia are a delighted bunch. Huge moment in the game

headshotImage.longCaption: Manish Pandey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Manish Pandey not out 104 (81b 8x4 1x6 129m) SR: 128.39
